        <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
          <tr>
          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          <b>Features</b>
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
The image below shows the front panel of the BMR-1000. At the centre
is a 6-digit frequency readout, built with red LED 7-segment displays.
To its right are three push buttons for TIME (gate timing), DIM
(reduced light) and LATCH (hold current frequency). To the left of the
display are three potentiometers: GAIN (input sensitivity), THRESHOLD
and VOLUME. The latter controls the volume of the rattle &mdash; a rattling sound
that increases with the strength of the intercepted signal.
<br />
          <br />
          <table 
           border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td align="center" valign=top>
<a href="img/303071/010/full.jpg">            <div style="position: relative;" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Click to see more">
<a href="img/303071/010/full.jpg">            <div style="position: relative;" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Click to see more">
            <img src="img/bmr1000_ext.png"
             style="
            "
             align="center"
             width="540px"
             vspace="4"
             alt="Click to see more"
             border=0
             />
            </div>
            </a>
            </td></tr><tr><td align=center>
          </td></tr></table>
<br />
The device is powered by a <span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Direct Current">DC</span> source between 10 and 15V &mdash; typically
the battery of a vehicle &mdash; that should be connected to the fixed red/black
wiring at the rear.
A stabilized 12V <span class="short tooltip-red" data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="Direct Current">DC</span> output for a peripheral device is available on
a 3 mm jack at the bottom left of the front panel.
<br />
<br />
          </font>
          </td></tr>
        </table>
<br />        <a name=int></a>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
          <tr>
          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          <b>Interior</b>
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
